The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, July 23, 2004 				 A profile in courage
																								Genuine human relationships should be forged on likeness of mind rather than on birth ties. However, in our so-called progressive society, relationships are based solely on social class. Kalindi Natya Srijans play Nona Raater Gaan reveals this dismal state of affairs most movingly through the solitary saga of Moyna, a young woman belonging to the weaker sections of society. Moyna struggles on her own to overcome the cruel twists of fate in her life only to be thwarted in her efforts by the village bigwigs, who are intent on exploiting this poor, defenceless woman. Her indomitable spirit and power of resilience enable her to rise above her tragic circumstances and begin life afresh with the support of those who empathise with her and help her regain hope of a better life ahead. Written by Anup Chakraborty and directed by Bilwadal Chatterjee, the play starkly exposes the social hypocrisy of our times.																								Event: Play in Bengali, Nona Raater Gaan, produced by Kalindi Natya Srijan 																								When: Today at 6.30 pm																								Where: Girish Mancha
